sql:
SELECT SUM(value) AS total_production_value_2022
FROM production_data
WHERE year = 2022;

SELECT SUM(value) AS total_value
FROM production_data
WHERE production_id = 0;

SELECT value
FROM production_data
WHERE production_id = 0 AND year = 2022;

SELECT SUM(value) AS total_production_value
FROM month_current
WHERE year = 2023;

external_knowledge:
- "Adjusted total production values" refers to the sum of monthly production values, with a 10% increase for 'agricultural' material types; 
- "Latest analytics result" refers to the most recent analytics result for each data type, which can be either 'result1' or NULL;
- The context assumes that the production data is being analyzed to evaluate the performance of different industries and material types over time.
